        google: { rating: 4.4, review_count: 52, maps_url: 'https://maps.google.com/?cid=2549655575304561888&g_mp=CiVnb29nbGUubWFwcy5wbGFjZXMudjEuUGxhY2VzLkdldFBsYWNlEAIYBCAA', reviews: [{author: '254Shad', rating: 1, text: 'So legacy just opened up recently in uptown, like a lot of you I was excited about trying it. I’ve went it and spent a lot of money on overpriced products, regardless I’m here to support the business. I’ve told my friends about it and people that I know just word of mouth. I started liking the Lite Og Indica strain , only one I like there. After the 2 time of grabbing it I started weighing it and ', time: 'a month ago'}, {author: 'Eric S Hungerford', rating: 5, text: 'Since the first day I was in town, these guys have been solid and consistent.  The staff is super helpful and friendly, and the strains I\'ve tried are pretty dang great. The gummies are also beyond delicious.  The glass shop is phenomenal, with all kinds of fun stuff from a whole lot of artists from pretty much everywhere.  And, to top it off, you can learn to blow glass and rent space to do it.  ', time: '4 weeks ago'}, {author: 'John Jacob Jingleheimer-Schmitt', rating: 5, text: 'I WILL DRIVE ANYWHERE FOR GOOD BUD Don\'t believe people who say they got a bag that was short.The weight was spot on flower looks amazing and tastes great.Grabbed some Lit OG.One of the best dispensaries there is.I am also a bud tender and value your quality product.The product is weighed and sealed so there is no way a bag can be short.I think it\'s sad people bad mouth such a great brand.Show the', time: '2 months ago'}, {author: 'Tara Plum', rating: 5, text: 'I\'ve only been there once so far but they have a great selection of flower, vapes, gummies, pre-rolls, etc.  Their "8ths" are 4 grams instead of 3.5 which is cool!  Most of their flower is available in higher quantities too.  It\'s also connected to a glass shop right next door with a huge selection.  The people working there are super friendly and laid back too!', time: 'a month ago'}, {author: 'MN Freedman', rating: 5, text: 'Great product! I think it’s mostly or all native / locally grown product which I love supporting as well. Much higher quality product than I was getting from the local suppliers with a medical base.  Super nice and knowledgeable people. Ronnie (I think that was his name) was awesome. They have locations in Minneapolis and Woodbury. This review is about the MPLS location.', time: '2 months ago'}] }
