        google: { rating: 4.4, review_count: 607, maps_url: 'https://maps.google.com/?cid=14048419485981313691&g_mp=CiVnb29nbGUubWFwcy5wbGFjZXMudjEuUGxhY2VzLkdldFBsYWNlEAIYBCAA', reviews: [{author: 'Mar', rating: 5, text: 'Updated:  June 27,2025 After trying the BW Cap Junky and seeing the 50% sale I was compelled to try BW Sour Jack. 🤤yum It claims a THC 20% but it felt like a 26%. Great aftertaste. It was packaged 2/2025 and I opened it today (photos).💚  Say hello and welcome new man TJ W. You’ll learn much from MJ.  June 21, 2025 I’ve never smoked any of the Boundary Waters flowers so I bought the Cap Junky Pre-r', time: '7 months ago'}, {author: 'Epsilon', rating: 5, text: 'Great selection, knowledgeable and friendly staff, fair prices (especially if you wait for promotions), neat and clean shop, free parking. Most of the pictures and reviews for Green Goods - Woodbury are actually this Green Goods in Downtown Minneapolis.', time: '3 months ago'}, {author: 'Michael Moser', rating: 4, text: 'Had a pretty ok selection to choose from. I wasn\'t super hyped up on the quality of the product but I know we\'re in the infancy stages of legal cannabis in MN so I\'m trusting the quality to improve soon. But otherwise easy location to get to, staff is extremely welcoming ànd knowledgeable. They are all very "real" and a total vibe.', time: 'a month ago'}, {author: 'Tara Andrews', rating: 1, text: 'If you buy something here, take it home, and it doesn\'t work... They will not honor the price you paid for an exchange.  I paid $150 for two all-in-one vapes. One didn\'t work. I called and was told they would exchange it.  What they don\'t tell you is that you have to pay the MUCH HIGHER exchange price (now $110 EACH) and that they WILL NOT HONOR the price you originally paid. So now I have no meds', time: 'a month ago'}, {author: 'Melissa Kelly', rating: 3, text: 'I recently received a medication order that was short by 0.5g. While I was given a $10 credit, I was told to contact the vendor (Rise / RYTHM) directly to report the issue.  As a business consultant, I believe it is Green Goods’ responsibility to escalate concerns with their partners and vendors, not the customer’s. In addition they should track to the frequency of this issue in general. During th', time: 'a month ago'}] }
